						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar of the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the natural cave known as Āṇḍār-maḍam on the hill.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Madi[rai*]koṇḍa Parakēsarivarman Year 19: 925-26 A.D. (Parāntaka I)</hi></p>						

						<p>This damaged inscription can be assigned to c. 10th Century on grounds of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It seems to refer to a gift by Viṇṇagar Vayiramēgaṉ to a Daśapuriyan, a Kāḷāmukha belonging to the Harita-gōtra and Āpastamba-sūtra. The other details are not clear as the record is incomplete.</p>						

						</summary>
